                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSomatotropin would not be administered during or after epiphyseal closure. Efficacy of therapy declines as the client ages and is usually lost entirely by age 20 to 24 years. The conditions in the remaining options are indications for use of the medication.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the word contraindicated. Note that options 1, 2, and 4 are comparable or alike, as they all relate to a child with growth failure. Note that the correct option is different because it identifies a client of a particular age.",
