                        "content": "Octreotide acetate is prescribed for a client with acromegaly. The nurse monitors the client, knowing that which side or adverse effect is associated with the administration of this medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nOctreotide is used to reduce growth hormone levels in clients with acromegaly. The most common side and adverse effects of octreotide are diarrhea, nausea, gallstone formation, and abdominal discomfort. Polyuria is not associated with this medication. Hypertension, although rare, may occur.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, side and adverse effects related to octreotide acetate. Knowledge regarding the side and adverse effects is required to answer the question. Remember that the most common side and adverse effects of octreotide are diarrhea, nausea, gallstone formation, and abdominal discomfort.",
                        "id": "388fedce61e44104b32fde1b83fc2788",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "312da7ddf4914422b551529fb6c92b07",
                                "content": "Hypocalciuria"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "7f4ee3ba3ae947138af186639fef7ccc",
                                "content": "Hypoglycemia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "eeaa311dfa4b46a9a62035a5b0b16bb7",
                                "content": "Hyperglycemia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e898a456be9c4fab8519457cf1a38155",
                                "content": "Hyperthyroidism"
