                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHyperglycemia can occur as a result of the administration of growth hormone, particularly in a client with diabetes mellitus. Hypercalciuria can occur, particularly during the first 2 to 3 months of therapy. Growth hormone therapy is associated with a decline in thyroid function.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, an adverse effect of hormone replacement therapy. Note that options 2 and 3 are opposites; this may indicate that one of them is correct. Remember that hyperglycemia can occur as a result of the administration of growth hormone.",
