                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nGrowth hormone may be used in the treatment of dwarfism. When treatment is started, height may be increased by as much as 6 inches. The increase is immediate and continual. To monitor treatment, height and weight would be measured monthly. All other options indicate delayed or sporadic increases in growth, which are incorrect.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, the action of growth hormone. Eliminate options that identify lengthy and specific time frames related to the expected outcome of the medication.",
